<br>
I have a pretty general question for all of you in higher end guilds.<br>
<br>
I am currently a proud member of a very friendly yet growing guild.  We pretty much have a NBG raid loot policy.  My question is what really defines NEED?  On a recent guild/ally raid in Kael, we had a corroded BP drop.   There were like 10-15 plate class raiders there.  Our MA was a lvl 60 warrior that still does not have Champions BP i believe, also had a 60 SK also.  A few others 55+ including me.  <br>
<br>
Of course every plate class who was a main got to roll. And a 51 cleric won.  The cleric winning is not why I am concerned, she is valuable ally and I congratulate her.  <br>
<br>
My question is should my guild perhaps start changing some of its loot policies so that we can better equp those that need upgrades, i.e I personally think the BP should have gone to the 60 Warrior or SK.<br>
<br>
Im not trying to be biased or anything, in fact I think a general NBG loot policy is perhaps the fairest, especiall for guild like mine.  Im just trying to learn how best to suggest changes that could benifit my guild as a whole?<br>
<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
<br>
<br>
