<br>
The main tank for that guild was an incredible man..he knew his stuff in every zone in the game at the time, he grinded XP constantly and he was a very capable raid leader...but he saw BP after BP go to people who had been in the guild a week or people it didn't benefit as much as the MT.  He left to join the server's uberguild, and the process of equipping a MT started all over again (I was playing my necro at the time).  I started saying that maybe we should look into officer awarded loot, because at the rate we were going we were NEVER going to get out of Kael.  Quite a few people agreed with me, but the guild leadership didn't.  I quit a couple days later, after telling them they'd spend the rest of their days farming Kael.<br>
<br>
Guild broke up 2 months after that, and most people quit EQ.  It was a goddamned shame because they were the best people I've ever played EQ with..ruined by random loot. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
