<br>
A pure merit system where the officers default everything to whoever they decide should get it can work but only if the officers are completely fair about it and everyone in the guild trusts their judgement.  That's pretty rare IMHO.  In most cases a system like that degenerates into a good old boy system where the core members get all the good stuff and everyone else gets leftovers.<br>
<br>
With a points based system the old timers do have first shot at everything, but new people that regularly attend raids and save up their points can get the good stuff too.  As other people mentioned a points system can also degrade into a state where the old timers get all the good stuff and everyone else gets scraps.  The way around this is to make the point values on items high enough that people who win small upgrades frequently end up spending so many points that they fall into the same point category as the new recruits.  That encourages people to spend points on big upgrades and forgoe the insignificant ones.<br>
<br>
As an example, my guild uses sort of a combination point/lotto system.  We have tiers based on points and when something drops anyone within 4 tiers of the highest to enter the lotto can roll on it.  The tiers are worth increasingly more points so the first tiers are easy to climb through and the final tiers are much harder.  So old timers who don't spend their points frivolously can lock people out of rolling on stuff they really want, but by the same token new recruits that save up their points can climb the tiers and eventually roll against the old timers.<br>
<br>
I am fairly new to my guild, but have resolved to only spend points on the stuff I really want.  Because of this out of a roster of about 12 warriors there are only 2 that I can't roll against after only being in the guild 2 months.  By the same token since I am still in a relatively low tier every upgrade I get knocks me back down significantly in tiers.  I won a BoC recently and it cost me half my points and dropped me 3 tiers.  That basically put me out of the running for anything else I wanted for about 3 weeks but I've saved my points and now I'm back in the running again uless the 2 old timers I can't roll against yet want it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=472195">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
