<br>
Just like your job. You wouldn't expect to make the same money working 30 hours a week as the guy next to you doing the same job working 40 hours a week.<br>
<br>
Random is a good way to start out a guild but once you start to raid you need to dump that. Merit works well for some but how do you do that without any bias? Points works best imo because you take something away at the end of the raid even if you didn't win something and it motivates people to attend more often. (although I would attend anyway because I love to raid) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91997" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://xtctripp101.homestead.com/files/sigs/Brudal_sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
